In [[differential geometry]], the '''Bochner–Yano theorem''' states that the [[isometry group]] of a compact [[Riemannian manifold]] with negative [[Ricci curvature]] is finite. It is named after its publication by {{harvs|last1=Bochner| |first1=Salomon|author1-link=Salomon Bochner |last2=Yano|first2=Kentaro|author2-link=Kentaro Yano (mathematician)|year=1953|txt}}.

