In [[mathematics]], '''Shimura's reciprocity law''', introduced by {{harvs|txt|last=Shimura|authorlink=Goro Shimura|year=1971}}, describes the action of [[idele]]s of [[imaginary quadratic field]]s on the values of [[modular function]]s at [[singular moduli]].  It forms a part of the [[Kronecker Jugendtraum]], explicit [[class field theory]] for such fields.  There are also higher-dimensional generalizations.

